Description: McNamee Law - CrunchBase
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: David McNamee, a Beavercreek attorney and founder of the McNamee Law Office, serves residents throughout the Miami Valley and surrounding areas of Ohio. McNamee Law prides itself on treating clients with courtesy, professionalism, and promptness, while making sure they fully understand each stage of the process. Mr. McNamee believes that straightforward case management is best for all those involved, which means setting achievable, realistic expectations. Founded in 1997, McNamee Law specializes in all aspects of family law, including divorce, adoption, child support, and paternity issues. In addition, McNamee Law can assist clients with misdemeanor cases, such as traffic offenses and license suspensions, as well as real estate transactions. For companies interested in business law, the firm also offers personalized business organization support, such as incorporation and dissolution. David McNamee is a native of Xenia, Ohio, and graduated from Alter High School in 1988. Mr. McNamee went on to obtain his Bachelor’s degree in Mediterranean and Middle East Studies from the University of Notre Dame in 1994, graduating cum laude. David McNamee studied law at the University of Dayton for the next several years, during which time he served as an editor of the Law Review and argued cases before the Moot Court. Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: UniversityJunction provides an online connection to classmates through academic forums. The website also helps students complete their coursework more efficiently by allowing students to share what they think is most relevant to each course. The site is free to all students. The UniversityJunction team recognized the absence of any comprehensive study tools for undergraduate students across all disciplines and created an ethical site to fulfill the need. In essence, the goal is to provide a place where information can be shared, materials can be accessed and connections can be made so that a student can better understand and complete their courses successfully. The current features of the website include academic forums, a search function and a digital library full of student uploaded materials. The academic forums include the ability to post a question to a specific class or to a general subject, and are viewable by all users. The search function allows students to not only search the web, but also to search a digital library which is populated with various types of documents, links as well as audio and visual files.  Active student participation will help the website grow to benefit all users. UniversityJunction recognizes that each student needs to learn the same course material but have different learning methods, which is why new functions will gradually be implemented to suit the needs of all users.  UniversityJunction is currently available for tens of thousands of courses across 10 campuses throughout the United States and Canada. The network will continue to expand steadily to reach over 160,000 courses on 56 campuses by March, and 160 universities and colleges in total, by the end of 2009.
